<subSubSection id="C335C785FFBEFFB7FF3958ABEB2AFB7C" pageId="1" pageNumber="380" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B90940EFFBEFFB7FF3958ABED40FBC0" blockId="1.[151,1437,959,1238]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis id="B95B481CFFBEFFB7FF3958ABEF5EFC73" bold="true" box="[151,274,959,986]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Robust sharpshooters with head slightly produced and broadly rounded anteriorly; ocelli located behind imaginary line between anterior eye angles, each closer to adjacent anterior eye angle than to median line of crown; epistomal suture almost always entire. Forewing with coriaceous texture; veins distinct, often elevated. Male terminalia with connective in form of transverse bar (i.e., without stalk); paraphyses absent. Female terminalia with sternite VII bearing median posterior projection or lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90940EFFBEFFB7FF695F60EB2AFB7C" blockId="1.[151,1437,959,1238]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis id="B95B481CFFBEFFB7FF695F60EF4AFB27" bold="true" box="[199,262,1140,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">Note.</emphasis>
The external morphology (head and thorax) of the three new species herein described and of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2FEF8DFFBEFFB7FAAC5F60EBD0FB27" authorityName="Mejdalani &amp; Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1282,1436,1140,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unifasciata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95B481CFFBEFFB7FAAC5F60EBD0FB27" box="[1282,1436,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">A. unifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95B481CFFBEFFB7FF395F8CEF5AFB1B" bold="true" box="[151,278,1176,1202]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A268F567FFBEFFB7FF395F8CEF5AFB1B" box="[151,278,1176,1202]" pageId="1" pageNumber="380" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
agrees with the above diagnosis and with the detailed description of the genus provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBEE9FFFFBEFFB7FAAA5F8CEE82FB7F" author="Young, D. A." pageId="1" pageNumber="380" pagination="1 - 1135" refId="ref7297" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, i-vi + 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young (1977: 176)</bibRefCitation>
. Hence, in the descriptions below, we focus on the color pattern and the terminalia of males and females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
